---
description: Branch-aware behavior for mka-bootstrap maintainers vs consumers
alwaysApply: true
---

On branch `main` (mka-bootstrap maintainer context):
- Follow ROADMAP.md milestones for template product work
- Never run `./install.sh` except via `scripts/test/run-local-harness.sh`
- Use `publish-to-install.sh` to update the consumer `install` branch

On branch `install` (consumer context):
- `./install.sh` is the primary entry point
- README is the consumer install guide, not the maintainer product README
